<subSubSection lastPageId="67" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="66" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
The type of 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">
<pageBreakToken pageId="66" pageNumber="67" start="start">Elampus</pageBreakToken>
spina
</taxonomicName>
(Lepeletier) could be housed at MNHN or in the Spinola collection. A specimen of this species at MNHN is labelled: E. Panzeri F. &lt;handwritten by Lepeletier&gt; / 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Hedychrum spina</taxonomicName>
Lep. type? &lt;handwritten by du Buysson&gt; / Museum Paris Meudon (S. et. O.) Coll. Le Peletier 160-45 &lt;partially printed, locality handwritten by du Buysson&gt;. This specimen was not considered as a type by 
<bibRefCitation author="Buysson, R du" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="518 - 580" title="Etude des Chrysidides du Museum de Paris." volume="66" year="1898">du Buysson (1898</bibRefCitation>
: 563; 
<bibRefCitation author="Buysson, R du" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="159 - 169" title="Catalogue des Insectes Hymenopteres de la famille des Chrysidides du Museum de Paris." volume="5" year="1899">1899</bibRefCitation>
: 160), because when arrived at MNHN it was labelled only as 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus panzeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panzeri">Elampus panzeri</taxonomicName>
by Lepeletier, without locality or identification label. It perfectly matches the original description by Lepeletier and the colour drawing furnished by the author. We would nowadays identify this specimen as 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus constrictus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">Elampus constrictus</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar, L" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="439 - 447" title="Ueber die Notozus-Arten Ungarns (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae)." volume="56" year="1964 a">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Móczár">Moczar</normalizedToken>
1964a
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen in the Spinola collection could alternatively represent the type, but even in this case, there is no certainty. It perfectly matches 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lepeletier’s">Lepeletier's</normalizedToken>
description and it belongs to the species 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus constrictus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">Elampus constrictus</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) also.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lepeletier’s">Lepeletier's</normalizedToken>
description is clear: &quot;
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tête">Tete</normalizedToken>
et corcelet 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’un">d'un</normalizedToken>
vert 
<normalizedToken originalValue="bleuâtre">bleuatre</normalizedToken>
; yeux et antennes noirs. Corcelet 
<normalizedToken originalValue="très-prolongé">tres-prolonge</normalizedToken>
sous 
<normalizedToken originalValue="l’écusson">l'ecusson</normalizedToken>
. Abdomen 
<normalizedToken originalValue="doré">dore</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="troisième">troisieme</normalizedToken>
segment 
<normalizedToken originalValue="échancré">echancre</normalizedToken>
. Pieds 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’un">d'un</normalizedToken>
vert 
<normalizedToken originalValue="bleuâtre">bleuatre</normalizedToken>
; tarses 
<normalizedToken originalValue="pâle">pale</normalizedToken>
. Ailes 
<normalizedToken originalValue="à">a</normalizedToken>
peine 
<normalizedToken originalValue="enfumée">enfumee</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mâle">Male</normalizedToken>
. De Meudon&quot;. The description is completed by a colour drawing (pl. 6: 2) which shows a specimen with light green head and mesosoma, golden metasoma and small dimensions, being smaller than 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum nitidum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidum">Hedychrum nitidum</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga fervida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fervida">Holopyga fervida</taxonomicName>
] and 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum lucidum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidum">Hedychrum lucidum</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga lucida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucida">Holopyga lucida</taxonomicName>
], and approximately as long as 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium roseum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseum">Hedychridium roseum</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium roseum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseum">Hedychridium roseum</taxonomicName>
]. Description, colouration, and dimensions are different from the species considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 232" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies." volume="32" year="1959">Linsenmaier (1959)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar, L" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="433 - 450" title="Ergebnisse der Revision der Goldwespenfauna des Karpatenbeckens (Hymenoptera: Chrysididae)." volume="10" year="1964 b">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Móczár">Moczar</normalizedToken>
(1964b)
</bibRefCitation>
. This species is one of the largest 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Elampus</taxonomicName>
species (up to 9 mm) in Europe, with head and mesosoma dark blue to violet and with a flame red metasoma, sometimens dark red to red-violet on the lateral sides. Even the type locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
seems to be out from the current distributional limits of 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
sensu auctorum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
The misinterpretation of the species that the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
refers to started with 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Berlingianis, Lund" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales - Part II - Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano." year="1845">Dahlbom (1845</bibRefCitation>
: 41): Spinola sent a specimen to Dahlbom identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
(or 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus panzeri var. spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="panzeri" variety="spina">Elampus panzeri var. spina</taxonomicName>
), which he had received from Latreille, and that clearly differs from the specimen now placed in the Spinola collection under the name 
<taxonomicName lsidName="spina" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="spina">spina</taxonomicName>
Lep. coll. Latreille.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis, specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta ab Adrea Gustavo Dahlbom. Chrysis in sensu Linneano" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854</bibRefCitation>
: 42) did not describe 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
Lepeletier, but instead he described a new species received by Spinola and named 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
Spinola: &quot;Habitat in Gallia, a D. Latreille detectus, e cujus Collectione Illustr. Spinola accepit individuum quod describendi caussa mihi benevole misit&quot;. Dahlbom's description matches the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus bidens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidens">Elampus bidens</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853): &quot;Submagnus 2 1/4 lin. decimal. long. violascenti et purpurascenti-aeneus abdomine cyaneo-viridi, segmento 3:tio ante emarginatnram utrinque bisinuato postscutello mucronato&quot;.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<bibRefCitation author="Abeille de Perrin, E" journalOrPublisher="Marseille" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" title="Diagnoses de Chrysides nouvelles." year="1878">Abeille (1878</bibRefCitation>
: 1, 2) replaced the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom with 
<taxonomicName lsidName="superbus" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="superbus">superbus</taxonomicName>
(&quot;nomen 
<normalizedToken originalValue="à">a</normalizedToken>
changer&quot;). Both 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom and 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus superbus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superbus">Elampus superbus</taxonomicName>
Abeille are synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus bidens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidens">Elampus bidens</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Based on the type material examined in MNHN, HNHM, and LZM, the original description and drawing, 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
(Lepeletier) (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 232" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies." volume="32" year="1959">Linsenmaier 1959</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar, L" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="439 - 447" title="Ueber die Notozus-Arten Ungarns (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae)." volume="56" year="1964 a">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Móczár">Moczar</normalizedToken>
1964a
</bibRefCitation>
) is 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus frivaldszkyi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frivaldszkyi">Elampus frivaldszkyi</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) (= 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus productus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus">Elampus productus</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom, 1854); 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus constrictus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">Elampus constrictus</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) is the junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
(Lepeletier, 1806). We suggest the neotype designation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
and a revision of the European species, based on recent findings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Moreover, we note that 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus panzeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panzeri">Elampus panzeri</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1804) is the valid name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus scutellaris" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">Elampus scutellaris</taxonomicName>
(Panzer, 1798). A future revision of the European species belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Elampus</taxonomicName>
is already planned to put in order the complex taxonomical problems of this genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Since 1845 the name 
<taxonomicName lsidName="spina" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="spina">spina</taxonomicName>
has been considered as a noun and not as an adjective; in fact it was used as an invariable name in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Elampus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Ellampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ellampus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ellampus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1804" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1804" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Omalus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Omalus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Förster, 1853" authorityName="Förster" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Notozus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notozus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Notozus</taxonomicName>
in more than fifty publications. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kimsey, LS" journalOrPublisher="University Press, New York" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World." year="1991">Kimsey and Bohart (1991)</bibRefCitation>
introduced the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spinus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinus">Elampus spinus</taxonomicName>
in accordance with the genus gender, but in conflict with the historical interpretation of the name and the articles 23.5 (applications to spellings) and 33.3.1 of the ICZN (when an incorrect subsequent spelling is in prevailing usage and is attributed to the publication of the original spelling, the subsequent spelling and attribution are to be preserved and the spelling is deemed to be the correct original spelling).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<pageBreakToken pageId="67" pageNumber="68" start="start">Only</pageBreakToken>
three authors followed the interpretation given to the name by Kimsey and Bohart (
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spinus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinus">Elampus spinus</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tyrner, P" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, supplement" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="41 - 63" title="Chrysidoidea: Chrysididae (zlatenkoviti)." volume="11" year="2007">Tyrner 2007</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1804" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1804" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Omalus (Elampus) spinus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinus" subGenus="Elampus">Omalus (Elampus) spinus</taxonomicName>
(Arens 2014, 
<bibRefCitation pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Linsenmaier 1999</bibRefCitation>
)) while in other publications the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
remained in use (Liubomirov 2007, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mingo, E" journalOrPublisher="Museo Nacional de Cencias Naturales Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas, Madrid" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" title="HymenopteraChrysididae. Fauna Iberica." year="1994">Mingo 1994</bibRefCitation>
, Rosa 2005a, 2005b, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="- Pierre, Aosta" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" title="I Crisidi della Valle d'Aosta. Monografie del Museo regionale di Scienze naturali, St." year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="Doria &quot;" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="209 - 272" title="Catalogo dei Tipi dei Crisidi del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot; di Genova (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G." volume="100" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Strumia, F" editor="Minelli, A" journalOrPublisher="Calderini (Bologna)" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 10" title="HymenopteraChrysididae." volume="99" volumeTitle="Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana." year="1995">Strumia 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 2005, Strumia and Yildirim 2007, 2012, Strumia, Gayubo, Gonzalez 2010, Tussac and Zumeta 2004, Vinokurov 2008).
</paragraph>
